During a visit to the South Lawn, President Biden spoke to a group of children and their parents who were brought to work. He thanked his Secret Service agents and engaged with the children, answering their questions and sharing personal stories. The children asked about his experiences as President, his family, his favorite ice cream flavor, and more. President Biden expressed his hope for the next generation of Americans and discussed his accomplishments as President, including healthcare reform and infrastructure development. He also emphasized the importance of unity and America's unique foundation based on the idea of equality. The President ended the interaction by taking photos and shaking hands with the children before returning to the Oval Office.